# Internal release tooling — never ship to the public mirror.
# `git archive` (used by scripts/publish_public.py to build the public snapshot)
# honours export-ignore. The publisher's own scrub-pattern list contains the
# private research tokens it guards against, so exporting it would BOTH self-trip
# the fail-closed scrub gate AND leak that context. Keep it private-only.
scripts/publish_public.py export-ignore
